organization.description: The Federal Laboratory Consortium for Technology Transfer (FLC) is the nationwide network of federal laboratories that provides the forum to develop strategies and opportunities for linking laboratory mission technologies and expertise with the marketplace.
organization.title: Federal Laboratory Consortium

name: airborne-amp-field-sensors-facilities
notes: RTTC facilities include an 800&#39; x 60&#39; paved UAV operational area, clear approach/departure zone, concrete pads furnished with 208VAC, 3 phase, 200 amp power, 20,000 sq ft of climate controlled hanger space, with machine shop and integration facilities for sensors on fixed and rotary wing aircraft. Substantial ground sensor testing ranges are available, complete with range control facilities and a raised 5 meter mound with 18,200 sq ft work pad, 75&#39; tower and instrumented trailers. Stabilized airborne instrumentation platforms are also available, as well as a wide variety of target and non-target entities. Capabilities for collecting multi-spectral signatures, ground truthing TSPI information is available, as well as dispensing and characterizing obscurants for supporting detection/recognition tests and system-of-systems tests, over varied terrain. RTTC also has a unique reconfigurable underground 6&#39; concrete tunnel facility, with two connecting tunnels measuring 364&#39; and 100&#39; in length.
title: Airborne & Field Sensors Facilities
